text: Khalil Taha (13 July 1932 - 27 July 2020) was a Lebanese wrestler. At the 1951 Mediterranean Games in Alexandria Egypt, Taha won the silver medal in the 73 kg Greco-Roman wrestling. At the 1952 Summer Olympics, he won the bronze medal in the men's Greco-Roman Welterweight category. ==References== Category:1932 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Lebanese sportspeople Category:Olympic bronze medalists Category:Wrestlers
